Explanation:
- The RegisterRequestController.registerRequest method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/request/register", method = RequestMethod.POST), which means this endpoint only handles POST requests to the path /request/register. There is no class-level prefix shown, so no additional path segments are prepended.
- Since only POST is mapped for this path, all methods are not acceptable (false). HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, PUT, DELETE, and PATCH are also not supported by this method based on the code (false for each).
- There are other endpoints in the same controller (e.g., /request/accept/{id}, /request/reject/{printRequestID}, /requests/pending), but they do not alter the HTTP methods applicable to /request/register.
